import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.dropna(subset=['age'])
    plt.hist(data['age'], bins=20, color='blue', edgecolor='black')
    plt.axvline(data['age'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f'Median Age: {data["age"].median():.2f}')
    plt.xlabel('Age')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the age distribution of the victims?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    gender_counts = data['gender'].value_counts()
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.bar(gender_counts.index, gender_counts.values, color=['#1f77b4', '#ff7f0e'])
    ax.set_xlabel('Gender')
    ax.set_ylabel('Count')
    ax.set_title('What is the gender distribution of the victims?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.groupby('race').size().reset_index(name='counts')
    plt.bar(data['race'], data['counts'], color=['#1f77b4', '#ff7f0e', '#2ca02c', '#d62728'])
    plt.title('What is the racial distribution of the victims?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.copy()
    data = data.groupby('type').size().reset_index(name='counts')
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(6, 6))
    ax.pie(data['counts'], labels=data['type'], autopct='%1.1f%%', startangle=90)
    ax.axis('equal')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of the type of incidents?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.scatter(data['longitude'], data['latitude'], alpha=0.5)
    plt.xlabel('Longitude')
    plt.ylabel('Latitude')
    plt.title('What is the geographical distribution of the incidents?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
